ory:Fascism in the United States]]\n[[Category:Neo-fascist terrorist incidents in the United States]]\n[[Category:Political violence in the United States]]\n[[Category:Terrorist incidents in the United States in 2017]]\n[[Category:Terrorist incidents involving vehicular attacks]]\n[[Category:Terrorist incidents in Virginia]]\n[[Category:Terrorism in the United States]]\n[[Category:White nationalism in the United States]]\n[[Category:White supremacy in the United States]]\n[[Category:Vehicular rampage in the United States]]\n[[Category:White nationalist terrorism]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-pc1}}\n{{short description|Vehicle-ramming attack in the United States}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2018}}{{Coord|38|01|46.17|N|78|28|46.29|W|display=title}}\n{{Infobox civilian attack\n| title         = Charlottesville terror attack\n| partof        = \n| image         =<!-- see [[Kent State shootings]] for a similar article where a Pulitzer Prize-winning non-free photograph appears in the infobox --> 2017 Charlottesville, Virginia car attack photograph.jpg\n| image_size    = \n| image_upright =\n| alt           = Photograph of the 2017 Charlottesville vehicle-ramming attack\n| caption       = [[Pulitzer Prize for Breaking News Photography|Pulitzer Prize\u2013winning photograph]] of the attack taken by [[Ryan Kelly (photojournalist)|Ryan Kelly]] for ''[[The Daily Progress]]''\n| map_size      = \n| map_alt       = \n| map_caption   = \n| location      = Southern half of the [[Downtown Mall]], [[Charlottesville, Virginia]]\n| target = Crowd counter-protesting [[Unite the Right rally]]<ref name=\"nyt-fields\">{{cite news|work=The New York Times|date=August 13, 2017|first1=Jonah|last1=Bromwich|first2=Alan|last2=Blinder|title=What We Know About James Alex Fields Jr., Driver Charged in Charlottesville Killing|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/08/13/us/james-alex-fields-charlottesville-driver-.html|url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170813205813/https://www.nytimes.com